{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
df_labels = pd.read_csv('labels.csv')
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dls = ImageDataLoaders.from_df(df_labels, fn_col='fname', 
                               label_col='label',
                               valid_pct=0.3, 
                               item_tfms=Resize(256),
                               bs=64)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
dls.show_batch()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn = cnn_learner(dls, 
                    resnet34, 
                    metrics=[F1Score(),Precision(), Recall(), accuracy],
                    cbs=[SaveModelCallback(monitor='f1_score'),WandbCallback()]).to_fp16()
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn.path = path
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
learn.fine_tune(20, 1e-3, freeze_epochs=5, 
                cbs=[EarlyStoppingCallback(monitor='f1_score', patience=5)])

Now we have a model with fairly okay performance we can use it to classify if new images predicted as maps are actually maps according to our newly trained classifier.

{% raw %} 
from nnanno.inference import *
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
predictor = nnPredict(learn, try_gpu=True)
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
predictor

nnPredict 
learner vocab:['map', 'no_map']
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
predictor.predict_sample('maps', '/content/drive/MyDrive/Models/maps_nnanno', 
                         0.2, size=(512,512), end_year=1925, force_dir=True)
{% endraw %}
